00:23:45.760 --> 00:23:48.070 align:middle line:84%
These bands were
attached with Velcro,

00:23:48.070 --> 00:23:51.041 align:middle line:84%
so they could not be removed
without attracting attention.

00:23:51.041 --> 00:23:53.870 align:middle line:90%


00:23:53.870 --> 00:23:57.850 align:middle line:84%
They'd also requested the use
of night vision equipment.

00:23:57.850 --> 00:24:03.130 align:middle line:84%
>>We persistently asked them
to accept infrared cameras.

00:24:03.130 --> 00:24:05.330 align:middle line:90%
And they said, not yet.

00:24:05.330 --> 00:24:08.470 align:middle line:84%
It would interfere with
the energy in some way.

00:24:08.470 --> 00:24:11.320 align:middle line:84%
So we had to accept this
with great reluctance.

00:24:11.320 --> 00:24:13.430 align:middle line:84%
>>We were told that
this phenomena could

00:24:13.430 --> 00:24:15.090 align:middle line:90%
be developed in the light.

00:24:15.090 --> 00:24:17.720 align:middle line:84%
But if it were, it would
take an awfully long time

00:24:17.720 --> 00:24:20.850 align:middle line:84%
to produce-- years and years
rather than the few months

00:24:20.850 --> 00:24:23.610 align:middle line:90%
that it actually took us.

00:24:23.610 --> 00:24:26.840 align:middle line:84%
>>Critics saw this insistence
on darkness as an excuse

00:24:26.840 --> 00:24:28.090 align:middle line:90%
to hide fraud.

00:24:28.090 --> 00:24:30.280 align:middle line:84%
But participants to
the Scole experiment

00:24:30.280 --> 00:24:32.966 align:middle line:84%
were not always
in total darkness.

00:24:32.966 --> 00:24:34.454 align:middle line:90%
>>Whoa, look at you.

00:24:34.454 --> 00:24:37.926 align:middle line:90%
[CHATTERING]

00:24:37.926 --> 00:24:41.398 align:middle line:90%


00:24:41.398 --> 00:24:43.089 align:middle line:90%
>>Wow.

00:24:43.089 --> 00:24:44.630 align:middle line:10%
>>They were various
shapes, generally

00:24:44.630 --> 00:24:46.750 align:middle line:10%
like a pea-sized light.

00:24:46.750 --> 00:24:47.770 align:middle line:10%
And they had substance.

00:24:47.770 --> 00:24:51.880 align:middle line:10%
They would come and sit on
your hand, you could feel them.

00:24:51.880 --> 00:24:54.750 align:middle line:10%
>>They were intelligently
directed and intelligently

00:24:54.750 --> 00:24:58.210 align:middle line:10%
moving, and would be
responsive to our wishes,

00:24:58.210 --> 00:25:01.590 align:middle line:10%
whether expressed or silent.

00:25:01.590 --> 00:25:04.990 align:middle line:10%
>>The gyrations were
sometimes so rapid,

00:25:04.990 --> 00:25:09.830 align:middle line:10%
that it almost left like, a
circle of light going over

00:25:09.830 --> 00:25:10.890 align:middle line:10%
here and over there.

00:25:10.890 --> 00:25:14.860 align:middle line:84%
Sometimes two lights would
appear and just stare at me

00:25:14.860 --> 00:25:16.750 align:middle line:90%
within inches of my eyes.

00:25:16.750 --> 00:25:18.250 align:middle line:10%
>>I thought at first
that the lights

00:25:18.250 --> 00:25:20.830 align:middle line:10%
must be a small light
emitting diode suspended

00:25:20.830 --> 00:25:23.470 align:middle line:10%
on the end of
nylon fishing line.

00:25:23.470 --> 00:25:25.990 align:middle line:84%
>>Then suddenly, a
light would start

00:25:25.990 --> 00:25:28.490 align:middle line:84%
to do a tap dance on
the table, bouncing

00:25:28.490 --> 00:25:30.790 align:middle line:90%
up and down on the table.

00:25:30.790 --> 00:25:34.710 align:middle line:84%
And you could hear it click as
it rebounded from the table.

00:25:34.710 --> 00:25:35.510 align:middle line:10%
And suddenly--

00:25:35.510 --> 00:25:37.880 align:middle line:10%
>>It went pop, went
through the table,

00:25:37.880 --> 00:25:39.520 align:middle line:10%
and came out the other side.

00:25:39.520 --> 00:25:43.260 align:middle line:84%
Now, no nylon fishing
line explanation

00:25:43.260 --> 00:25:45.450 align:middle line:84%
would account for it going
through an apparently

00:25:45.450 --> 00:25:49.020 align:middle line:84%
solid-- well, it was a
solid object, a table.

00:25:49.020 --> 00:25:51.820 align:middle line:10%
>>The lights also had
another rather strange trick

00:25:51.820 --> 00:25:54.666 align:middle line:10%
up their sleeve, if I may talk
about lights as having sleeves.

00:25:54.666 --> 00:25:56.770 align:middle line:84%
And that was to
pass through bodies.

00:25:56.770 --> 00:25:59.640 align:middle line:10%
>>I was actually used as a
Guinea pig in the early days

00:25:59.640 --> 00:26:03.340 align:middle line:10%
to see how it felt and
to develop the phenomena.

00:26:03.340 --> 00:26:06.250 align:middle line:84%
And this light would actually
enter through my chest,

00:26:06.250 --> 00:26:08.270 align:middle line:84%
and then three minutes
later, it would probably

00:26:08.270 --> 00:26:11.610 align:middle line:84%
pop out of the arm or something,
and disappear across a room.

00:26:11.610 --> 00:26:14.774 align:middle line:84%
This was being developed to
produce a heating phenomena.

00:26:14.774 --> 00:26:16.440 align:middle line:10%
>>I have this bad
knee, and at one point

00:26:16.440 --> 00:26:18.540 align:middle line:10%
we had a light that was
moving around the room

00:26:18.540 --> 00:26:20.880 align:middle line:10%
and rested on my
knee for a, minute

00:26:20.880 --> 00:26:23.539 align:middle line:10%
and suddenly moved
inside my knee.

00:26:23.539 --> 00:26:25.080 align:middle line:10%
Yeah, she just went
into my bad knee.

00:26:25.080 --> 00:26:27.190 align:middle line:10%
[CHATTERING]

00:26:27.190 --> 00:26:29.070 align:middle line:90%


00:26:29.070 --> 00:26:30.980 align:middle line:10%
I could feel it moving
around in my knee,

00:26:30.980 --> 00:26:33.290 align:middle line:10%
and then all of a sudden
shot out the back of my leg

00:26:33.290 --> 00:26:34.090 align:middle line:10%
and took off.

00:26:34.090 --> 00:26:37.560 align:middle line:10%
The pain was greatly
reduced, and the swelling

00:26:37.560 --> 00:26:39.570 align:middle line:10%
that had been in it
that day was gone.

00:26:39.570 --> 00:26:44.190 align:middle line:84%
And then that was a huge,
wonderful thing to happen.

00:26:44.190 --> 00:26:47.290 align:middle line:10%
>>Visitors declared themselves
delighted by these displays,

00:26:47.290 --> 00:26:49.180 align:middle line:10%
but they were astonished
to hear voices

00:26:49.180 --> 00:26:52.570 align:middle line:10%
of what they say were
spirit personalities talking

00:26:52.570 --> 00:26:53.960 align:middle line:10%
through the mediums.

00:26:53.960 --> 00:26:57.370 align:middle line:84%
>>We had a thousand
hours of communication

00:26:57.370 --> 00:27:00.040 align:middle line:84%
during the Scole
Experiment, a thousand

00:27:00.040 --> 00:27:02.440 align:middle line:84%
hours of continuous
communication with the spirit

00:27:02.440 --> 00:27:02.880 align:middle line:90%
world.

00:27:02.880 --> 00:27:03.460 align:middle line:90%
>>Be quiet.

00:27:03.460 --> 00:27:03.632 align:middle line:90%
Be quiet.

00:27:03.632 --> 00:27:03.806 align:middle line:90%
Be quiet.

00:27:03.806 --> 00:27:04.900 align:middle line:90%
>>Shh.

00:27:04.900 --> 00:27:07.830 align:middle line:10%
>>Emily, when did you
live on the Earth?

00:27:07.830 --> 00:27:10.380 align:middle line:10%
>>19th century?

00:27:10.380 --> 00:27:13.310 align:middle line:10%
>>In this dramatic form
of spirit communication,

00:27:13.310 --> 00:27:16.100 align:middle line:10%
the mediums go into
trance, during which time

00:27:16.100 --> 00:27:20.952 align:middle line:10%
they say spirits take over their
bodies and speak through them.

00:27:20.952 --> 00:27:22.700 align:middle line:10%
>>It's the love
which makes people.

00:27:22.700 --> 00:27:23.570 align:middle line:10%
>>Yes.

00:27:23.570 --> 00:27:25.060 align:middle line:10%
Right.

00:27:25.060 --> 00:27:26.957 align:middle line:84%
>>And the rest
doesn't matter a jot.

00:27:26.957 --> 00:27:29.880 align:middle line:90%


00:27:29.880 --> 00:27:32.150 align:middle line:84%
>>So what's it like
to supposedly talk

00:27:32.150 --> 00:27:33.790 align:middle line:90%
to the dead in this way?

00:27:33.790 --> 00:27:35.200 align:middle line:90%
>>It becomes very natural.

00:27:35.200 --> 00:27:38.790 align:middle line:84%
And actually, talking to
somebody who is deceased,

00:27:38.790 --> 00:27:42.610 align:middle line:84%
if you like, is a natural
thing, purely and simply

00:27:42.610 --> 00:27:46.090 align:middle line:84%
because it's the same as you
talking to me here in this room

00:27:46.090 --> 00:27:47.240 align:middle line:90%
at this very moment.

00:27:47.240 --> 00:27:49.290 align:middle line:84%
There's no difference,
other than the fact

00:27:49.290 --> 00:27:52.462 align:middle line:84%
that we are aware that they're
no longer in this world.

00:27:52.462 --> 00:27:54.940 align:middle line:84%
>>And not be
frightened in any way.

00:27:54.940 --> 00:27:57.550 align:middle line:84%
>>But could the mediums
have just been acting?

00:27:57.550 --> 00:28:00.005 align:middle line:90%
The researchers didn't think so.

00:28:00.005 --> 00:28:01.380 align:middle line:10%
>>The voices were
quite different

00:28:01.380 --> 00:28:03.970 align:middle line:10%
from those of the
mediums themselves,

00:28:03.970 --> 00:28:06.540 align:middle line:10%
and the personalities
behind the voices

00:28:06.540 --> 00:28:09.830 align:middle line:10%
were not only quite different,
but were very consistent,

00:28:09.830 --> 00:28:13.320 align:middle line:10%
even the accents were.

00:28:13.320 --> 00:28:15.150 align:middle line:84%
>>But it wasn't
just the consistency

00:28:15.150 --> 00:28:17.770 align:middle line:84%
of the accents that
impressed the researchers.

00:28:17.770 --> 00:28:19.910 align:middle line:84%
They reported that
the personalities also

00:28:19.910 --> 00:28:23.310 align:middle line:84%
remembered every detail of
all conversations spoken

00:28:23.310 --> 00:28:26.680 align:middle line:84%
to visitors over a
five-year period.

00:28:26.680 --> 00:28:30.750 align:middle line:84%
Add to those skills the
ability to read minds.

00:28:30.750 --> 00:28:33.050 align:middle line:10%
This apparently occurred
when the female spirit

00:28:33.050 --> 00:28:34.155 align:middle line:10%
spoke to the group.

00:28:34.155 --> 00:28:36.030 align:middle line:84%
>>She would tell us what
was going to happen.

00:28:36.030 --> 00:28:37.990 align:middle line:84%
She would comment on
what we were doing,

00:28:37.990 --> 00:28:40.080 align:middle line:84%
and sometimes what
we were thinking.

00:28:40.080 --> 00:28:42.630 align:middle line:84%
She would answer our
questions quite frequently

00:28:42.630 --> 00:28:45.910 align:middle line:84%
before we had actually
asked them, which was

00:28:45.910 --> 00:28:47.890 align:middle line:90%
quite embarrassing sometimes.

00:28:47.890 --> 00:28:50.087 align:middle line:10%
>>Thank you for your
warm appreciation,

00:28:50.087 --> 00:28:52.420 align:middle line:10%
what you're trying to do.

00:28:52.420 --> 00:28:54.690 align:middle line:10%
>>This communicator
identified herself

00:28:54.690 --> 00:28:57.690 align:middle line:10%
as the spirit of a
Mrs. Emily Bradshaw.

00:28:57.690 --> 00:29:00.110 align:middle line:84%
>>And Mrs. Bradshaw,
who is a very commanding

00:29:00.110 --> 00:29:06.120 align:middle line:84%
figure, a lady of the
upper class Victorian

00:29:06.120 --> 00:29:07.600 align:middle line:90%
or Edwardian lady.

00:29:07.600 --> 00:29:09.280 align:middle line:90%
She sounded like that.

00:29:09.280 --> 00:29:11.490 align:middle line:10%
>>We continue from
our side of life

00:29:11.490 --> 00:29:16.700 align:middle line:10%
to influence people
still in the body.

00:29:16.700 --> 00:29:19.490 align:middle line:84%
>>But what evidence was there
that these voices were really

00:29:19.490 --> 00:29:20.940 align:middle line:90%
from the deceased?

00:29:20.940 --> 00:29:22.620 align:middle line:10%
>>We knew that we
were communicating

00:29:22.620 --> 00:29:26.740 align:middle line:10%
with deceased personalities,
because a number of people

00:29:26.740 --> 00:29:30.210 align:middle line:10%
who communicated with us
were able to be identified

00:29:30.210 --> 00:29:35.090 align:middle line:10%
by independent witnesses at
the time who could testify as

00:29:35.090 --> 00:29:37.770 align:middle line:10%
to them being people
they knew, evidence

00:29:37.770 --> 00:29:41.500 align:middle line:10%
which couldn't possibly have
been known by anybody else.

00:29:41.500 --> 00:29:43.000 align:middle line:84%
>>But what's it
like for the mediums

00:29:43.000 --> 00:29:45.410 align:middle line:84%
to have these ethereal
communicators speak

00:29:45.410 --> 00:29:46.710 align:middle line:90%
through them?

00:29:46.710 --> 00:29:50.970 align:middle line:84%
>>Those sensations become
more and more intense

00:29:50.970 --> 00:29:56.000 align:middle line:84%
and build up to a point where
I feel the personality actually

00:29:56.000 --> 00:29:58.995 align:middle line:90%
taking part of my senses over.

00:29:58.995 --> 00:30:02.490 align:middle line:84%
I become more and more
unaware of my own body,

00:30:02.490 --> 00:30:04.930 align:middle line:84%
and also more and more
unaware of my own thoughts.

00:30:04.930 --> 00:30:15.340 align:middle line:90%


00:30:15.340 --> 00:30:17.370 align:middle line:84%
>>My mother died about
a year and a half

00:30:17.370 --> 00:30:19.180 align:middle line:90%
before my father did.

00:30:19.180 --> 00:30:23.270 align:middle line:84%
And three days before
my father died,

00:30:23.270 --> 00:30:30.630 align:middle line:84%
he saw a vision of my mother,
and was very disturbed when

00:30:30.630 --> 00:30:32.370 align:middle line:90%
she suddenly disappeared.

00:30:32.370 --> 00:30:35.840 align:middle line:84%
And I believe that
his death coincided

00:30:35.840 --> 00:30:39.099 align:middle line:84%
with that vision of her and
wanting to see her again.

00:30:39.099 --> 00:30:52.090 align:middle line:90%


00:30:52.090 --> 00:30:55.130 align:middle line:84%
>>Back at Scole, visitors
reported seeing and especially

00:30:55.130 --> 00:30:57.960 align:middle line:84%
hearing these
objects materialize

00:30:57.960 --> 00:31:00.530 align:middle line:90%
from out of nowhere.

00:31:00.530 --> 00:31:02.500 align:middle line:84%
In the language of
physical mediumship,

00:31:02.500 --> 00:31:05.380 align:middle line:84%
these objects are
called apports.

00:31:05.380 --> 00:31:10.140 align:middle line:84%
>>An apport is an object,
which is quite solid,

00:31:10.140 --> 00:31:12.960 align:middle line:84%
which is brought
from one location

00:31:12.960 --> 00:31:16.580 align:middle line:84%
to another during an
experimental session,

00:31:16.580 --> 00:31:20.440 align:middle line:84%
but so show doing, apparently
passes through solid walls,

00:31:20.440 --> 00:31:22.626 align:middle line:90%
doors, et cetera.

00:31:22.626 --> 00:31:24.000 align:middle line:84%
Well, the total
number of apports

00:31:24.000 --> 00:31:27.470 align:middle line:84%
that we had during the
experimental sessions

00:31:27.470 --> 00:31:28.620 align:middle line:90%
was about 80 or even more.

00:31:28.620 --> 00:31:32.310 align:middle line:90%


00:31:32.310 --> 00:31:34.410 align:middle line:84%
Whilst we were sitting
here, this object

00:31:34.410 --> 00:31:37.660 align:middle line:84%
would arrive, just materialize,
and arrive on the table.

00:31:37.660 --> 00:31:40.104 align:middle line:84%
And as it arrived, [THUMP]
that's the sort of noise

00:31:40.104 --> 00:31:41.840 align:middle line:90%
it would make.

00:31:41.840 --> 00:31:44.390 align:middle line:84%
>>Despite the fact that
witnesses heard a loud bang

00:31:44.390 --> 00:31:47.700 align:middle line:84%
every time an apport
arrived, no matter how small,

00:31:47.700 --> 00:31:50.940 align:middle line:84%
skeptics have dismissed
this phenomenon as objects

00:31:50.940 --> 00:31:54.420 align:middle line:90%
merely thrown into the air.

00:31:54.420 --> 00:31:56.550 align:middle line:10%
But the appearance
of these apports

00:31:56.550 --> 00:31:59.820 align:middle line:10%
are not so easy to explain away.

00:31:59.820 --> 00:32:02.770 align:middle line:10%
These newspapers arrived
in pristine condition,

00:32:02.770 --> 00:32:06.480 align:middle line:10%
despite having
originated in the 1940s.

00:32:06.480 --> 00:32:11.580 align:middle line:84%
But who might have sent it
to the Scole Group, and why?

00:32:11.580 --> 00:32:13.350 align:middle line:84%
The answer arrived,
they say, when

00:32:13.350 --> 00:32:15.380 align:middle line:84%
dead British medium,
Helen Duncan,

00:32:15.380 --> 00:32:18.740 align:middle line:84%
spoke to them via
one of the mediums.

00:32:18.740 --> 00:32:20.480 align:middle line:84%
During World War
II, Duncan's life

00:32:20.480 --> 00:32:23.410 align:middle line:84%
was ruined when she was
arrested and imprisoned

00:32:23.410 --> 00:32:26.450 align:middle line:90%
for practicing mediumship.

00:32:26.450 --> 00:32:28.580 align:middle line:10%
As she described her
ordeal to the group,

00:32:28.580 --> 00:32:32.146 align:middle line:10%
this newspaper allegedly
appeared out of nowhere.

00:32:32.146 --> 00:32:33.800 align:middle line:90%
[THUMP]

00:32:33.800 --> 00:32:37.860 align:middle line:84%
To their astonishment, displayed
prominently on its front page,

00:32:37.860 --> 00:32:41.270 align:middle line:84%
was the story of Duncan's
trial and conviction.

00:32:41.270 --> 00:32:44.020 align:middle line:84%
>>I think she suffered
greatly for her mediumship.

00:32:44.020 --> 00:32:47.450 align:middle line:84%
And she was really
coming to wish us well.

00:32:47.450 --> 00:32:51.300 align:middle line:10%
And she brought the newspaper as
a sign of a very turbulent time

00:32:51.300 --> 00:32:52.930 align:middle line:10%
in her life.

00:32:52.930 --> 00:32:55.470 align:middle line:10%
>>The scientists knew that
an old newspaper could easily

00:32:55.470 --> 00:32:57.950 align:middle line:10%
be copied and printed
onto a modern paper,

00:32:57.950 --> 00:33:02.020 align:middle line:10%
so Montague Keen had the
suspect newspaper analyzed.

00:33:02.020 --> 00:33:05.990 align:middle line:84%
>>We took it to the leading
research station in England,

00:33:05.990 --> 00:33:09.190 align:middle line:84%
indeed in the world,
on paper and printing.

00:33:09.190 --> 00:33:11.270 align:middle line:84%
And it was absolutely
clear from their report

00:33:11.270 --> 00:33:15.070 align:middle line:84%
that, first of all, it was
done on letter press, which

00:33:15.070 --> 00:33:18.230 align:middle line:84%
has gone out of
existence virtually

00:33:18.230 --> 00:33:21.490 align:middle line:84%
since the early
1970s, I would say.

00:33:21.490 --> 00:33:24.610 align:middle line:84%
It was newsprint
produced during wartime,

00:33:24.610 --> 00:33:27.740 align:middle line:84%
which lacks certain chemicals,
which you couldn't get hold of.

00:33:27.740 --> 00:33:29.740 align:middle line:84%
So this was a genuine
article, which

00:33:29.740 --> 00:33:31.640 align:middle line:84%
appeared 50 years
after the event,

00:33:31.640 --> 00:33:34.520 align:middle line:84%
but no one has been able to
explain how it got there.

00:33:34.520 --> 00:33:37.530 align:middle line:84%
>>So where did all these
apported objects come from?

00:33:37.530 --> 00:33:39.330 align:middle line:84%
>>We were told by the
spirit team that they

00:33:39.330 --> 00:33:42.310 align:middle line:84%
were never stolen,
but basically objects

00:33:42.310 --> 00:33:45.690 align:middle line:84%
that had been lost or
discarded, or at one time been

00:33:45.690 --> 00:33:48.540 align:middle line:84%
owned by the spirit personality
that brought them for us.

00:33:48.540 --> 00:33:58.780 align:middle line:90%


00:33:58.780 --> 00:34:01.620 align:middle line:84%
>>Back in Italy, we
were given unique access

00:34:01.620 --> 00:34:05.510 align:middle line:84%
to film one of Bacci's
private seances.

00:34:05.510 --> 00:34:07.760 align:middle line:84%
>>I think, now you have
to sit somewhere, and sit

00:34:07.760 --> 00:34:08.560 align:middle line:90%
not in my bed.

00:34:08.560 --> 00:34:09.692 align:middle line:90%
Not in my bed.

00:34:09.692 --> 00:34:10.900 align:middle line:90%
Somewhere that you can, yes--

00:34:10.900 --> 00:34:12.780 align:middle line:84%
>>Despite the loss
of this camera,

00:34:12.780 --> 00:34:15.670 align:middle line:84%
we were allowed to continue
using this night shot

00:34:15.670 --> 00:34:18.139 align:middle line:84%
camera to record
the seance, which

00:34:18.139 --> 00:34:20.187 align:middle line:90%
took place in total darkness.

00:34:20.187 --> 00:34:21.020 align:middle line:90%
[NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

00:34:21.020 --> 00:34:23.520 align:middle line:90%
[SHUSHING]

00:34:23.520 --> 00:34:25.520 align:middle line:90%


00:34:25.520 --> 00:34:29.500 align:middle line:84%
>>As the seance progressed,
the medium went into trance.

00:34:29.500 --> 00:34:31.500 align:middle line:90%
[HEAVY BREATHING]

00:34:31.500 --> 00:34:34.460 align:middle line:90%
[GROANING]

00:34:34.460 --> 00:34:40.150 align:middle line:90%


00:34:40.150 --> 00:34:42.940 align:middle line:84%
>>We were hoping to capture
what visitors to Scole

00:34:42.940 --> 00:34:48.650 align:middle line:84%
said they had witnessed, the
levitation of solid objects.

00:34:48.650 --> 00:34:51.489 align:middle line:84%
However, minutes later, we
were asked to switch off

00:34:51.489 --> 00:34:53.620 align:middle line:90%
the night shot camera.

00:34:53.620 --> 00:34:56.460 align:middle line:84%
But secretly, we
kept it running.

00:34:56.460 --> 00:34:59.430 align:middle line:84%
And what we captured
was truly astonishing.

00:34:59.430 --> 00:35:02.570 align:middle line:84%
This heavy oak table
rose into the air.

00:35:02.570 --> 00:35:07.920 align:middle line:90%


00:35:07.920 --> 00:35:10.312 align:middle line:90%
[GROANING]

00:35:10.312 --> 00:35:12.214 align:middle line:90%
[STRANGE LAUGHING]

00:35:12.214 --> 00:35:16.500 align:middle line:90%


00:35:16.500 --> 00:35:19.060 align:middle line:84%
>>But levitations were
not the only phenomena

00:35:19.060 --> 00:35:20.955 align:middle line:84%
we witnessed during
these seances.

00:35:20.955 --> 00:35:24.050 align:middle line:90%


00:35:24.050 --> 00:35:27.410 align:middle line:84%
Like the Scole experiment,
visitors to Bacci's center

00:35:27.410 --> 00:35:31.310 align:middle line:84%
say they have received
apported objects.

00:35:31.310 --> 00:35:33.290 align:middle line:90%
This woman is one of them.

00:35:33.290 --> 00:35:53.250 align:middle line:90%


00:35:53.250 --> 00:35:56.650 align:middle line:84%
>>Once again, we were permitted
to use night shot cameras

00:35:56.650 --> 00:35:59.552 align:middle line:84%
in the hope of capturing
the arrival of an apport.

00:35:59.552 --> 00:36:02.330 align:middle line:90%
[GROANING]

00:36:02.330 --> 00:36:05.440 align:middle line:90%
We were not disappointed.

00:36:05.440 --> 00:36:07.860 align:middle line:84%
With the medium in
trance, the camera crew

00:36:07.860 --> 00:36:10.880 align:middle line:84%
were astonished
when, out of nowhere,

00:36:10.880 --> 00:36:13.619 align:middle line:84%
they felt these flowers
falling on them.

00:36:13.619 --> 00:36:15.056 align:middle line:90%
[NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

00:36:15.056 --> 00:36:16.014 align:middle line:90%
[GASPING]

00:36:16.014 --> 00:36:19.846 align:middle line:90%
[NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

00:36:19.846 --> 00:36:25.640 align:middle line:90%


00:36:25.640 --> 00:36:28.670 align:middle line:84%
>>With the lights on,
people reacted in amazement

00:36:28.670 --> 00:36:30.800 align:middle line:84%
at just how many
flowers had appeared.

00:36:30.800 --> 00:36:41.530 align:middle line:90%


00:36:41.530 --> 00:36:45.002 align:middle line:84%
>>As they collected them,
we continued our filming.

00:36:45.002 --> 00:36:46.340 align:middle line:90%
[CHATTERING]

00:36:46.340 --> 00:36:52.080 align:middle line:90%


00:36:52.080 --> 00:36:54.280 align:middle line:84%
Although we saw no
signs of trickery,

00:36:54.280 --> 00:36:59.870 align:middle line:84%
this seance was not conducted
under controlled conditions.

00:36:59.870 --> 00:37:03.470 align:middle line:84%
Therefore, critics could claim
it was possible for someone

00:37:03.470 --> 00:37:05.970 align:middle line:84%
to have thrown the
flowers into the room.

00:37:05.970 --> 00:37:07.600 align:middle line:90%
>>[NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

00:37:07.600 --> 00:37:09.120 align:middle line:90%


00:37:09.120 --> 00:37:12.220 align:middle line:84%
>>But apports which have a
specific connection to departed

00:37:12.220 --> 00:37:16.340 align:middle line:84%
loved ones frequently appear
at the Center, connections

00:37:16.340 --> 00:37:19.440 align:middle line:84%
that Bacci has no
previous knowledge of.

00:37:19.440 --> 00:37:21.450 align:middle line:10%
>>[NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

00:37:21.450 --> 00:37:40.140 align:middle line:90%


00:37:40.140 --> 00:37:42.420 align:middle line:84%
>>This woman said
that a single red rose

00:37:42.420 --> 00:37:44.015 align:middle line:90%
was apported into her hand.

00:37:44.015 --> 00:37:46.590 align:middle line:90%


00:37:46.590 --> 00:37:50.120 align:middle line:84%
She was also convinced it
came from her dead son,

00:37:50.120 --> 00:37:53.800 align:middle line:84%
because every week, she told us,
she placed an identical flower

00:37:53.800 --> 00:37:54.620 align:middle line:90%
on his grave.

00:37:54.620 --> 00:38:00.120 align:middle line:90%


00:38:00.120 --> 00:38:03.590 align:middle line:84%
As impossible as it sounds,
could this rose really

00:38:03.590 --> 00:38:05.630 align:middle line:84%
have been sent from
the other side?

00:38:05.630 --> 00:38:13.257 align:middle line:90%


00:38:13.257 --> 00:38:15.340 align:middle line:84%
>>I'm not sure that I do
believe in the afterlife.

00:38:15.340 --> 00:38:19.977 align:middle line:84%
I think it's because I'd like
to have final rest when I die

00:38:19.977 --> 00:38:22.560 align:middle line:84%
rather than have to think about
coming back as something else.

00:38:22.560 --> 00:38:29.890 align:middle line:90%


00:38:29.890 --> 00:38:34.710 align:middle line:84%
>>Back at Scole, the phenomena
were continuing to progress.

00:38:34.710 --> 00:38:37.320 align:middle line:84%
The scientists were about to
experience something even more

00:38:37.320 --> 00:38:38.470 align:middle line:90%
shocking.

00:38:38.470 --> 00:38:41.392 align:middle line:10%
>>Another thing that happened
was that a hand materialized

00:38:41.392 --> 00:38:42.210 align:middle line:10%
and sort of glowed.

00:38:42.210 --> 00:38:44.990 align:middle line:10%


00:38:44.990 --> 00:38:48.320 align:middle line:10%
And there was this disembodied
hand floating around.

00:38:48.320 --> 00:38:50.120 align:middle line:84%
When I told some of
my friends about it,

00:38:50.120 --> 00:38:53.060 align:middle line:84%
they said it sounded just
like The Addams Family.

00:38:53.060 --> 00:38:54.450 align:middle line:90%
And I commented to the medium.

00:38:54.450 --> 00:38:56.880 align:middle line:84%
I said, oh, I can see
a disembodied hand.

00:38:56.880 --> 00:38:58.720 align:middle line:84%
And she said, it's
not disembodied.

00:38:58.720 --> 00:39:01.140 align:middle line:84%
This was Mrs. Bradshaw,
who was speaking

00:39:01.140 --> 00:39:02.990 align:middle line:90%
through one of the mediums.

00:39:02.990 --> 00:39:05.560 align:middle line:84%
And I said, you mean there's
an invisible body attached?

00:39:05.560 --> 00:39:06.767 align:middle line:90%
And she said precisely.

00:39:06.767 --> 00:39:08.850 align:middle line:84%
And then she said, would
you like it to touch you?

00:39:08.850 --> 00:39:09.650 align:middle line:90%
And I said yes.

00:39:09.650 --> 00:39:11.620 align:middle line:90%
So she said, well, ask it.

00:39:11.620 --> 00:39:14.470 align:middle line:84%
So I said hand,
will you touch me?

00:39:14.470 --> 00:39:16.426 align:middle line:84%
And so the hand went
around behind me,

00:39:16.426 --> 00:39:17.800 align:middle line:84%
and it tapped me
on the shoulder.

00:39:17.800 --> 00:39:20.600 align:middle line:90%


00:39:20.600 --> 00:39:23.330 align:middle line:10%
>>But could these
hands have been hoaxed?

00:39:23.330 --> 00:39:25.610 align:middle line:84%
This visitor who felt
the truncated length

00:39:25.610 --> 00:39:28.310 align:middle line:84%
of a disembodied
arm didn't think so.

00:39:28.310 --> 00:39:30.430 align:middle line:10%
>>And I was so startled,
I moved my hand,

00:39:30.430 --> 00:39:32.462 align:middle line:10%
and it traveled
right up a sleeve.

00:39:32.462 --> 00:39:34.170 align:middle line:84%
There was a sleeve,
like a cotton sleeve,

00:39:34.170 --> 00:39:36.670 align:middle line:84%
very much like this,
right up to the shoulder,

00:39:36.670 --> 00:39:37.720 align:middle line:90%
and then it just stopped.

00:39:37.720 --> 00:39:40.219 align:middle line:84%
There was nothing beyond where
the shoulder would have been.

00:39:40.219 --> 00:39:43.300 align:middle line:84%
It was a really
amazing experience.

00:39:43.300 --> 00:39:44.300 align:middle line:90%
>>Is it a hand?

00:39:44.300 --> 00:39:45.100 align:middle line:90%
Oh, yes, yes.

00:39:45.100 --> 00:39:46.300 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:39:46.300 --> 00:39:47.800 align:middle line:90%
>>Yeah, it's a hand.

00:39:47.800 --> 00:39:50.240 align:middle line:90%
[CHATTERING]

00:39:50.240 --> 00:39:51.088 align:middle line:90%
>>Oh, I see it.

00:39:51.088 --> 00:39:52.180 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:39:52.180 --> 00:39:54.470 align:middle line:84%
>>Sometimes, we would be
touched by these hands.

00:39:54.470 --> 00:39:56.740 align:middle line:84%
Sometimes, we would
invite them to touch us.

00:39:56.740 --> 00:39:59.600 align:middle line:84%
Sometimes, they would touch
us on our knees, let's say,

00:39:59.600 --> 00:40:02.150 align:middle line:84%
or on our feet, which as
it was a fraud proof table,

00:40:02.150 --> 00:40:04.840 align:middle line:84%
were inaccessible to
the mediums themselves.

00:40:04.840 --> 00:40:08.340 align:middle line:10%
>>So what's it like to touch
one of these spirit hands?

00:40:08.340 --> 00:40:12.330 align:middle line:10%
>>It felt cool, but not cold.

00:40:12.330 --> 00:40:13.360 align:middle line:90%
It didn't feel clammy.

00:40:13.360 --> 00:40:14.480 align:middle line:90%
It didn't feel slimy.

00:40:14.480 --> 00:40:16.560 align:middle line:84%
It felt like a
normal human hand,

00:40:16.560 --> 00:40:18.800 align:middle line:90%
and it grasped my hand firmly.

00:40:18.800 --> 00:40:21.480 align:middle line:10%
>>The unseen communicators
told the scientists

00:40:21.480 --> 00:40:24.680 align:middle line:10%
that they usually
materialized a hand or an arm

00:40:24.680 --> 00:40:28.170 align:middle line:10%
because it was easier than
materializing a full body.

00:40:28.170 --> 00:40:30.740 align:middle line:10%
But some cases of full
bodies being materialized

00:40:30.740 --> 00:40:32.090 align:middle line:10%
were reported.

00:40:32.090 --> 00:40:34.550 align:middle line:84%
>>I had the presence,
the physical presence,

00:40:34.550 --> 00:40:38.190 align:middle line:84%
of my mother, my
father, and my sister,

00:40:38.190 --> 00:40:41.210 align:middle line:84%
all in solid form standing
in front of me, all of whom

00:40:41.210 --> 00:40:44.330 align:middle line:84%
I was able to hold,
to embrace, carry out

00:40:44.330 --> 00:40:45.710 align:middle line:90%
conversations with them.

00:40:45.710 --> 00:40:50.880 align:middle line:84%
I witnessed it so many times,
it just becomes a normal thing.

00:40:50.880 --> 00:40:54.002 align:middle line:10%
>>Normal is a word strained by
the experiences of the Scole

00:40:54.002 --> 00:40:54.802 align:middle line:10%
experiment.

00:40:54.802 --> 00:40:58.110 align:middle line:90%


00:40:58.110 --> 00:41:00.730 align:middle line:84%
And there was nothing
normal when patches of light

00:41:00.730 --> 00:41:02.930 align:middle line:84%
floated over the
scientists' heads

00:41:02.930 --> 00:41:06.469 align:middle line:84%
and slowly changed
into spectral forms.

00:41:06.469 --> 00:41:08.010 align:middle line:84%
>>The diffused
patches of light would

00:41:08.010 --> 00:41:11.470 align:middle line:84%
take the form just of human
face, moving around the room,

00:41:11.470 --> 00:41:14.460 align:middle line:84%
with the direct voice
very, very faintly

00:41:14.460 --> 00:41:16.510 align:middle line:84%
coming from the
diffused patch of light,

00:41:16.510 --> 00:41:19.250 align:middle line:84%
and the lips moving,
again, very faintly.

00:41:19.250 --> 00:41:22.340 align:middle line:90%


00:41:22.340 --> 00:41:25.590 align:middle line:10%
>>As I stared at the face,
it was noticeably smaller

00:41:25.590 --> 00:41:28.500 align:middle line:10%
than a normal size head.

00:41:28.500 --> 00:41:31.922 align:middle line:84%
But within the faces itself,
features were clearly visible.

00:41:31.922 --> 00:41:33.630 align:middle line:84%
You could see the
glistening of the eyes.

00:41:33.630 --> 00:41:36.042 align:middle line:90%
We could see the eyes moving.

00:41:36.042 --> 00:41:39.730 align:middle line:84%
And even more remarkable
forms were to appear.

00:41:39.730 --> 00:41:44.043 align:middle line:90%
They looked like angelic forms.

00:41:44.043 --> 00:41:47.494 align:middle line:90%
[CHATTERING]

00:41:47.494 --> 00:41:49.959 align:middle line:90%


00:41:49.959 --> 00:41:50.945 align:middle line:90%
>>Oh, my goodness.

00:41:50.945 --> 00:41:52.930 align:middle line:90%
>>Would you look at that.

00:41:52.930 --> 00:41:56.300 align:middle line:10%
>>And I was very fortunate one
came and landed on my hand.

00:41:56.300 --> 00:42:03.010 align:middle line:90%


00:42:03.010 --> 00:42:06.030 align:middle line:84%
>>And just the energy
that you felt from it

00:42:06.030 --> 00:42:10.830 align:middle line:84%
when it connected with you
was a lovely experience.

00:42:10.830 --> 00:42:15.128 align:middle line:84%
And it just felt like an
overwhelming feeling of love.

00:42:15.128 --> 00:42:17.940 align:middle line:90%


00:42:17.940 --> 00:42:19.710 align:middle line:84%
>>These are great
experiences, you see.

00:42:19.710 --> 00:42:22.940 align:middle line:84%
Again, I must stress, it
changes your paradigm.

00:42:22.940 --> 00:42:25.780 align:middle line:84%
You go in thinking none
of this can be true.

00:42:25.780 --> 00:42:28.990 align:middle line:84%
But after an experience after
experience after experience,

00:42:28.990 --> 00:42:30.740 align:middle line:84%
it gradually dawns
on you, hey, there's

00:42:30.740 --> 00:42:32.300 align:middle line:84%
something going on
here that we can't

00:42:32.300 --> 00:42:35.817 align:middle line:84%
explain by normal
scientific laws,

00:42:35.817 --> 00:42:37.025 align:middle line:90%
but which nevertheless exist.

00:42:37.025 --> 00:42:45.280 align:middle line:90%


00:42:45.280 --> 00:42:47.882 align:middle line:84%
>>Years ago, I was staying
in this very old inn,

00:42:47.882 --> 00:42:51.155 align:middle line:84%
and I actually saw somebody
come out from the wall

00:42:51.155 --> 00:42:55.550 align:middle line:84%
and walk through, and
just disappear again.

00:42:55.550 --> 00:42:58.120 align:middle line:84%
And I just believe
there are people

00:42:58.120 --> 00:43:00.782 align:middle line:84%
that are trapped between
here and the next world.

00:43:00.782 --> 00:43:12.350 align:middle line:90%


00:43:12.350 --> 00:43:15.040 align:middle line:84%
>>The experiments
featured in this program

00:43:15.040 --> 00:43:17.890 align:middle line:84%
have been described by the
scientists who witnessed them

00:43:17.890 --> 00:43:23.900 align:middle line:84%
as some of the best evidence
for life after death ever.

00:43:23.900 --> 00:43:25.940 align:middle line:84%
After two years
of intense effort,

00:43:25.940 --> 00:43:28.860 align:middle line:84%
the Scole Experiment began
to produce more phenomena

00:43:28.860 --> 00:43:31.650 align:middle line:84%
than in any mediumship
experiment in the history

00:43:31.650 --> 00:43:33.580 align:middle line:90%
of the paranormal.

00:43:33.580 --> 00:43:36.460 align:middle line:84%
>>Their initial claims were
that they were in contact

00:43:36.460 --> 00:43:41.640 align:middle line:84%
with a group of deceased
entities who were producing,

00:43:41.640 --> 00:43:44.514 align:middle line:84%
with their help, a
number of pictures

00:43:44.514 --> 00:43:50.120 align:middle line:84%
of either deceased persons
or strips of films, which

00:43:50.120 --> 00:43:52.600 align:middle line:84%
they claimed to be produced
without any cameras

00:43:52.600 --> 00:43:54.260 align:middle line:90%
and in the dark.

00:43:54.260 --> 00:43:56.940 align:middle line:84%
>>To eliminate any
possibility of hoaxing,

00:43:56.940 --> 00:43:58.870 align:middle line:84%
the scientists
brought their own film

00:43:58.870 --> 00:44:02.270 align:middle line:84%
and locked it in a specially
designed security box.

00:44:02.270 --> 00:44:06.050 align:middle line:84%
>>The box was held in the
hands of the investigators,

00:44:06.050 --> 00:44:08.200 align:middle line:90%
so that no one could get at it.

00:44:08.200 --> 00:44:09.930 align:middle line:84%
And then immediately
afterwards, we

00:44:09.930 --> 00:44:11.950 align:middle line:84%
would take it out
of the box ourselves

00:44:11.950 --> 00:44:14.790 align:middle line:84%
so that no one else touched it,
and then develop it ourselves

00:44:14.790 --> 00:44:17.030 align:middle line:90%
in a special machine.

00:44:17.030 --> 00:44:20.150 align:middle line:84%
>>Despite all these
precautions, the experiments

00:44:20.150 --> 00:44:24.200 align:middle line:84%
continued to produce the
incredible images seen here.

00:44:24.200 --> 00:44:40.620 align:middle line:90%


00:44:40.620 --> 00:44:44.520 align:middle line:84%
>>They were able to achieve
whole lengths of film,

00:44:44.520 --> 00:44:47.440 align:middle line:84%
sometimes up to as
much as four feet,

00:44:47.440 --> 00:44:50.550 align:middle line:84%
with various words,
symbols, messages--

00:44:50.550 --> 00:44:53.800 align:middle line:84%
all sorts of different
things on that films.

00:44:53.800 --> 00:44:57.800 align:middle line:84%
>>Other firms contained poems
and centuries old German

00:44:57.800 --> 00:45:02.850 align:middle line:84%
and fragments of Greek,
Chinese, Hebrew, Latin, and even

00:45:02.850 --> 00:45:04.070 align:middle line:90%
Sanskrit.

00:45:04.070 --> 00:45:06.060 align:middle line:84%
The Scole group
were ordinary people

00:45:06.060 --> 00:45:07.850 align:middle line:84%
with no knowledge
of these languages.

00:45:07.850 --> 00:45:16.078 align:middle line:90%


00:45:16.078 --> 00:45:18.100 align:middle line:84%
But did these films
have a purpose?

00:45:18.100 --> 00:45:21.230 align:middle line:84%
If dead personalities were
producing these images,

00:45:21.230 --> 00:45:24.190 align:middle line:84%
why did they apparently
design some of them

00:45:24.190 --> 00:45:26.060 align:middle line:90%
as complex puzzles?

00:45:26.060 --> 00:45:28.410 align:middle line:84%
>>Providing something
which is a puzzle, which

00:45:28.410 --> 00:45:31.157 align:middle line:84%
is difficult to solve
is simply because it

00:45:31.157 --> 00:45:33.240 align:middle line:84%
is difficult to solve, it
isn't readily available.

00:45:33.240 --> 00:45:36.580 align:middle line:84%
It can't be easily attributable
to the person sitting

00:45:36.580 --> 00:45:39.620 align:middle line:90%
around the table.

00:45:39.620 --> 00:45:41.600 align:middle line:84%
>>Despite lengthy
investigations,

00:45:41.600 --> 00:45:43.900 align:middle line:84%
the possible authors
of some of the films,

00:45:43.900 --> 00:45:48.260 align:middle line:84%
like this German poem,
proved impossible to trace.

00:45:48.260 --> 00:45:50.800 align:middle line:84%
But others were
easier to track down.

00:45:50.800 --> 00:45:54.020 align:middle line:84%
This one contains a
poem by Frederick Myers.

00:45:54.020 --> 00:45:57.230 align:middle line:84%
Intriguingly, Myers is one
of the founders of the SPR,

00:45:57.230 --> 00:46:00.420 align:middle line:84%
and a passionate researcher
into the evidence

00:46:00.420 --> 00:46:01.490 align:middle line:90%
for life after death.

00:46:01.490 --> 00:46:05.530 align:middle line:90%


00:46:05.530 --> 00:46:09.060 align:middle line:84%
Before he died in 1901,
he promised his colleagues

00:46:09.060 --> 00:46:11.480 align:middle line:84%
at the SPR that he
would try to communicate

00:46:11.480 --> 00:46:13.850 align:middle line:90%
with them from the other side.

00:46:13.850 --> 00:46:15.790 align:middle line:84%
Could this film
actually represent

00:46:15.790 --> 00:46:18.615 align:middle line:84%
evidence of the afterlife
sent by one of its greatest

00:46:18.615 --> 00:46:19.415 align:middle line:90%
investigators?

00:46:19.415 --> 00:46:22.500 align:middle line:90%


00:46:22.500 --> 00:46:24.720 align:middle line:84%
Mostly the researchers
were unclear as

00:46:24.720 --> 00:46:27.520 align:middle line:84%
to who might have
created these films.

00:46:27.520 --> 00:46:31.200 align:middle line:84%
However, there were clues as to
who the ghostly authors might

00:46:31.200 --> 00:46:34.400 align:middle line:84%
be in the form of
initials, or signatures.

00:46:34.400 --> 00:46:36.500 align:middle line:84%
For example in this
film, the signature

00:46:36.500 --> 00:46:41.030 align:middle line:84%
appears to belong to the dead
singer and actor Ivor Novello.

00:46:41.030 --> 00:46:43.700 align:middle line:84%
This was received on
one of the Scole films.

00:46:43.700 --> 00:46:45.951 align:middle line:10%
Compare it to Novello's
actual signature.

00:46:45.951 --> 00:46:50.610 align:middle line:90%


00:46:50.610 --> 00:46:55.160 align:middle line:84%
Investigators say these images
were created in total darkness,

00:46:55.160 --> 00:46:56.230 align:middle line:90%
but how?

00:46:56.230 --> 00:46:58.640 align:middle line:84%
>>I think that
those pictures can

00:46:58.640 --> 00:47:04.310 align:middle line:84%
be explained only by imagining
that the spirits can project

00:47:04.310 --> 00:47:08.650 align:middle line:84%
their recollections and images
onto a film in some way we

00:47:08.650 --> 00:47:11.390 align:middle line:90%
can't begin to understand.

00:47:11.390 --> 00:47:14.390 align:middle line:84%
The only alternative explanation
is they are all fakes,

00:47:14.390 --> 00:47:17.849 align:middle line:84%
but I don't believe that there's
evidence that that is the case.

00:47:17.849 --> 00:47:19.640 align:middle line:10%
>>Although the mechanism
for their creation

00:47:19.640 --> 00:47:23.690 align:middle line:10%
remains a mystery, investigators
concluded they were unique.

00:47:23.690 --> 00:47:25.380 align:middle line:84%
>>As far as the
photographic evidence

00:47:25.380 --> 00:47:27.510 align:middle line:84%
is concerned at Scole,
the strips of film,

00:47:27.510 --> 00:47:30.680 align:middle line:84%
there has, in my view, never
been anything like that at all

00:47:30.680 --> 00:47:31.480 align:middle line:90%
ever.

00:47:31.480 --> 00:47:35.720 align:middle line:90%


00:47:35.720 --> 00:47:37.360 align:middle line:84%
>>As far as I'm
aware, I don't think

00:47:37.360 --> 00:47:39.823 align:middle line:84%
there is any scientific
evidence for life after death.

00:47:39.823 --> 00:47:50.460 align:middle line:90%


00:47:50.460 --> 00:47:52.750 align:middle line:84%
>>Spurred on by the
photographic experiments,

00:47:52.750 --> 00:47:55.440 align:middle line:84%
the Scole group began a
series of video experiments

00:47:55.440 --> 00:47:58.230 align:middle line:84%
called Project
Alice, after "Alice

00:47:58.230 --> 00:48:01.070 align:middle line:90%
Through the Looking Glass."

00:48:01.070 --> 00:48:04.490 align:middle line:84%
Their ambition was nothing
less than to try and capture

00:48:04.490 --> 00:48:08.480 align:middle line:84%
moving images sent
from the spirit world.

00:48:08.480 --> 00:48:10.900 align:middle line:84%
The Scole group insists
that instructions

00:48:10.900 --> 00:48:13.700 align:middle line:84%
on how to position
the camera and mirrors

00:48:13.700 --> 00:48:16.550 align:middle line:84%
came from their
spirit communicators.

00:48:16.550 --> 00:48:19.770 align:middle line:10%
They were told to set up a
video camera in the dark cellar,

00:48:19.770 --> 00:48:22.330 align:middle line:10%
aim it at a pair of mirrors,
so that it could only

00:48:22.330 --> 00:48:23.905 align:middle line:10%
film its own viewfinder.

00:48:23.905 --> 00:48:27.490 align:middle line:90%


00:48:27.490 --> 00:48:30.550 align:middle line:84%
While it was recording,
nothing unusual was seen.

00:48:30.550 --> 00:48:32.810 align:middle line:84%
But when the tape
was played back,

00:48:32.810 --> 00:48:34.420 align:middle line:84%
these remarkable
pictures appeared.

00:48:34.420 --> 00:48:37.580 align:middle line:90%


00:48:37.580 --> 00:48:41.260 align:middle line:84%
>>We had images on
the video, sometimes

00:48:41.260 --> 00:48:43.985 align:middle line:84%
of what looked like
on a tunnel of light.

00:48:43.985 --> 00:48:47.170 align:middle line:90%


00:48:47.170 --> 00:48:50.330 align:middle line:84%
Other times, spirit faces
were coming towards us.

00:48:50.330 --> 00:48:55.280 align:middle line:90%


00:48:55.280 --> 00:48:57.960 align:middle line:84%
Sometimes, what appeared
to be a doorway moving.

00:48:57.960 --> 00:49:03.780 align:middle line:90%


00:49:03.780 --> 00:49:08.020 align:middle line:84%
>>Skeptics claim these images
were created by video feedback

00:49:08.020 --> 00:49:13.110 align:middle line:84%
occurring when a camera
records its own output.

00:49:13.110 --> 00:49:15.450 align:middle line:84%
But scientists have
ruled this out.

00:49:15.450 --> 00:49:21.530 align:middle line:84%
Video feedback doesn't
produce this kind of result.

00:49:21.530 --> 00:49:25.620 align:middle line:84%
As to what these extraordinary
pictures represent, we can only

00:49:25.620 --> 00:49:28.010 align:middle line:84%
guess, since their
meaning was never

00:49:28.010 --> 00:49:32.050 align:middle line:90%
explained to the Scole Group.

00:49:32.050 --> 00:49:35.220 align:middle line:84%
This video, also
totally unexplained,

00:49:35.220 --> 00:49:39.295 align:middle line:84%
appears to be a ghostly
face with moving eyes.

00:49:39.295 --> 00:49:42.090 align:middle line:90%


00:49:42.090 --> 00:49:46.260 align:middle line:84%
Later, a few video experiments
were attempted in full light.

00:49:46.260 --> 00:49:50.010 align:middle line:84%
Again, nothing unusual was
seen during the recording.

00:49:50.010 --> 00:49:53.370 align:middle line:84%
However, on playback, this
otherworldly figure appeared.

00:49:53.370 --> 00:50:04.140 align:middle line:90%


00:50:04.140 --> 00:50:06.190 align:middle line:84%
But was it possible
for the Scole Group

00:50:06.190 --> 00:50:08.490 align:middle line:90%
to have faked these images?

00:50:08.490 --> 00:50:09.940 align:middle line:84%
Not according to
the investigator

00:50:09.940 --> 00:50:13.670 align:middle line:84%
who monitored these experiments,
Swiss lawyer and businessman,

00:50:13.670 --> 00:50:15.012 align:middle line:90%
Doctor Hans Schaer.

00:50:15.012 --> 00:50:16.470 align:middle line:84%
>>There's absolutely
no possibility

00:50:16.470 --> 00:50:20.336 align:middle line:84%
that the film could have
been prepared before,

00:50:20.336 --> 00:50:24.167 align:middle line:84%
because I selected one
of the video films, which

00:50:24.167 --> 00:50:27.275 align:middle line:84%
was in its original
packaging, which I opened.

00:50:27.275 --> 00:50:28.735 align:middle line:90%
I took the film out.

00:50:28.735 --> 00:50:31.360 align:middle line:84%
I signed the film, and I put it
personally in the video camera.

00:50:31.360 --> 00:50:34.720 align:middle line:90%


00:50:34.720 --> 00:50:37.470 align:middle line:84%
>>He inserted it
into the camera.

00:50:37.470 --> 00:50:42.420 align:middle line:84%
We never touched at any
stage the camera or the film.

00:50:42.420 --> 00:50:44.848 align:middle line:10%
>>When he played the film,
it showed at the beginning

00:50:44.848 --> 00:50:49.640 align:middle line:10%
a number of bubbles
of various colors.

00:50:49.640 --> 00:51:02.550 align:middle line:90%


00:51:02.550 --> 00:51:05.030 align:middle line:84%
>>But there was one
particular bubble on there

00:51:05.030 --> 00:51:07.900 align:middle line:84%
in which the face of
a person appeared,

00:51:07.900 --> 00:51:10.230 align:middle line:84%
and it was a man
with spectacles.

00:51:10.230 --> 00:51:14.470 align:middle line:84%
>>Although Dr. Schaer did
not recognize this face,

00:51:14.470 --> 00:51:17.020 align:middle line:84%
the Scole Group thought
it might have belonged

00:51:17.020 --> 00:51:19.140 align:middle line:84%
to someone who was
trying to communicate

00:51:19.140 --> 00:51:20.585 align:middle line:90%
with him from the afterlife.

00:51:20.585 --> 00:51:27.167 align:middle line:90%


00:51:27.167 --> 00:51:29.250 align:middle line:84%
>>I have heard of the
electronic voice phenomenon.

00:51:29.250 --> 00:51:32.430 align:middle line:84%
I think it's actually one of the
most disturbing and unnerving

00:51:32.430 --> 00:51:36.682 align:middle line:84%
aspects of the notion of
there being an afterlife.

00:51:36.682 --> 00:51:39.860 align:middle line:90%
[FEEDBACK]

00:51:39.860 --> 00:51:43.450 align:middle line:84%
>>Attempting to capture spirit
voices via technical devices

00:51:43.450 --> 00:51:46.340 align:middle line:84%
like radios and tape recorders
has a long tradition that

00:51:46.340 --> 00:51:49.180 align:middle line:90%
goes back to the last century.

00:51:49.180 --> 00:51:51.140 align:middle line:84%
Today, there are
tens of thousands

00:51:51.140 --> 00:51:53.140 align:middle line:84%
of people around
the world who say

00:51:53.140 --> 00:51:55.160 align:middle line:84%
they have captured
the voices of the dead

00:51:55.160 --> 00:51:56.600 align:middle line:90%
on simple tape recorders.

00:51:56.600 --> 00:52:01.880 align:middle line:90%


00:52:01.880 --> 00:52:06.400 align:middle line:10%
This is known as the electronic
voice phenomena, or EVP,

00:52:06.400 --> 00:52:09.700 align:middle line:10%
and was recently popularized in
the Hollywood blockbuster White

00:52:09.700 --> 00:52:10.500 align:middle line:10%
Noise.

00:52:10.500 --> 00:52:17.420 align:middle line:90%


00:52:17.420 --> 00:52:19.770 align:middle line:84%
Despite the Hollywood
treatment, EVP

00:52:19.770 --> 00:52:24.010 align:middle line:84%
has been the focus of serious
scientific investigation.

00:52:24.010 --> 00:52:27.240 align:middle line:84%
One of the leading researchers
is Alexander McRae,

00:52:27.240 --> 00:52:30.250 align:middle line:84%
an electronics engineer who
has worked on communication

00:52:30.250 --> 00:52:32.260 align:middle line:90%
systems for the space shuttle.

00:52:32.260 --> 00:52:35.870 align:middle line:84%
He has been investigating
EVP for decades.

00:52:35.870 --> 00:52:38.200 align:middle line:84%
>>If somebody came up to
me in the street and said,

00:52:38.200 --> 00:52:40.690 align:middle line:84%
there's nothing paranormal
about EVP, I would say,

00:52:40.690 --> 00:52:43.880 align:middle line:84%
well, I've done at least
20 years and hundreds

00:52:43.880 --> 00:52:47.780 align:middle line:84%
of experiments, and I know
that it is paranormal effect.

00:52:47.780 --> 00:52:50.040 align:middle line:84%
Now how many experiments
have you done?

00:52:50.040 --> 00:52:52.400 align:middle line:10%
>>But skeptics
insist that EVP is

00:52:52.400 --> 00:52:56.220 align:middle line:10%
nothing more than the random
pick up of broadcast signals,

00:52:56.220 --> 00:52:59.020 align:middle line:10%
like radio and TV.

00:52:59.020 --> 00:53:01.860 align:middle line:84%
To test this theory,
McCrae try to obtain

00:53:01.860 --> 00:53:05.980 align:middle line:84%
EVP inside a laboratory
that was fully shielded

00:53:05.980 --> 00:53:08.500 align:middle line:90%
against radio and sound waves.

00:53:08.500 --> 00:53:12.370 align:middle line:84%
This meant it was impossible
to pick up any stray broadcast

00:53:12.370 --> 00:53:13.230 align:middle line:90%
signals.

00:53:13.230 --> 00:53:16.980 align:middle line:84%
>>So inside the laboratory,
you couldn't pick up anything.

00:53:16.980 --> 00:53:19.120 align:middle line:84%
But yet the device
still produced voices.

00:53:19.120 --> 00:53:23.430 align:middle line:90%


00:53:23.430 --> 00:53:26.990 align:middle line:84%
>>Although this audio sample
is hard to understand,

00:53:26.990 --> 00:53:29.060 align:middle line:84%
the very fact that
it was recorded

00:53:29.060 --> 00:53:31.475 align:middle line:84%
defies all known
laws of science.

00:53:31.475 --> 00:53:35.970 align:middle line:90%


00:53:35.970 --> 00:53:38.550 align:middle line:84%
One experimenter of
EVP is Vicky Talbot,

00:53:38.550 --> 00:53:42.940 align:middle line:84%
who lost her son Braden in
a boating accident in 2001.

00:53:42.940 --> 00:53:43.740 align:middle line:90%
>>OK.

00:53:43.740 --> 00:53:47.160 align:middle line:84%
I'm coming down into
Wildcat Cove right now,

00:53:47.160 --> 00:53:52.090 align:middle line:84%
which is the Cove that my
son departed from and did not

00:53:52.090 --> 00:53:52.890 align:middle line:90%
return.

00:53:52.890 --> 00:53:57.210 align:middle line:90%


00:53:57.210 --> 00:54:00.340 align:middle line:84%
>>Ever since then, she says
she can record and recognize

00:54:00.340 --> 00:54:02.379 align:middle line:84%
his voice using this
digital recorder.

00:54:02.379 --> 00:54:06.690 align:middle line:90%


00:54:06.690 --> 00:54:08.230 align:middle line:90%
>>Well, that's Braden.

00:54:08.230 --> 00:54:13.230 align:middle line:84%
What has really convinced
me is the way he speaks,

00:54:13.230 --> 00:54:14.895 align:middle line:90%
the stress, the intonation.

00:54:14.895 --> 00:54:18.150 align:middle line:90%


00:54:18.150 --> 00:54:21.850 align:middle line:84%
Sometimes, he sounds
exactly as he did in life.

00:54:21.850 --> 00:54:22.734 align:middle line:90%
>>Happy New Year.

00:54:22.734 --> 00:54:25.390 align:middle line:90%


00:54:25.390 --> 00:54:31.750 align:middle line:10%
>>He will use certain
phrases that we used to use.

00:54:31.750 --> 00:54:33.510 align:middle line:84%
>>He will say
certain things that

00:54:33.510 --> 00:54:38.715 align:middle line:84%
will identify himself as the
person that he was in life.

00:54:38.715 --> 00:54:43.230 align:middle line:90%


00:54:43.230 --> 00:54:49.940 align:middle line:84%
>>I am convinced personally that
I am communicating with my son.

00:54:49.940 --> 00:54:53.220 align:middle line:84%
>>Like visitors to Scole
and to Bacci's center,

00:54:53.220 --> 00:54:56.590 align:middle line:84%
EVP practitioners find
comfort in the belief

00:54:56.590 --> 00:54:59.165 align:middle line:84%
that they can still
communicate with loved ones.

00:54:59.165 --> 00:55:01.960 align:middle line:90%


00:55:01.960 --> 00:55:04.430 align:middle line:84%
>>But even this
conviction can't make up

00:55:04.430 --> 00:55:07.930 align:middle line:84%
for the unbearable
burden of losing a child.

00:55:07.930 --> 00:55:11.050 align:middle line:84%
>>These just make me want
to cry, just looking at him.

00:55:11.050 --> 00:55:13.900 align:middle line:90%


00:55:13.900 --> 00:55:19.990 align:middle line:84%
He'll just never be this
age again, or do that again.

00:55:19.990 --> 00:55:25.630 align:middle line:84%
What matters is the love that
you have for your family.

00:55:25.630 --> 00:55:29.940 align:middle line:84%
That's what really matters,
and not to screw it up,

00:55:29.940 --> 00:55:32.570 align:middle line:84%
and to remember they
could be gone in a flash.

00:55:32.570 --> 00:55:37.920 align:middle line:90%


00:55:37.920 --> 00:55:41.280 align:middle line:84%
>>You know, these other people,
I feel so sorry for them,

00:55:41.280 --> 00:55:45.590 align:middle line:84%
because they have no way
of communicating with those

00:55:45.590 --> 00:55:47.290 align:middle line:90%
that they have lost.

00:55:47.290 --> 00:55:53.250 align:middle line:84%
