is what we've done
here, the way we've

00:58:54.420 --> 00:58:57.040 align:middle line:84%
affected the people about us,
and the things that we do,

00:58:57.040 --> 00:58:58.390 align:middle line:90%
and it lives on through them.

00:58:58.390 --> 00:59:04.342 align:middle line:90%


00:59:04.342 --> 00:59:07.260 align:middle line:84%
>>Spirit voices speaking
through the mediums.

00:59:07.260 --> 00:59:11.510 align:middle line:84%
Spirit communication written
on sealed film in locked boxes.

00:59:11.510 --> 00:59:13.870 align:middle line:84%
All of these
incredible phenomena.

00:59:13.870 --> 00:59:16.490 align:middle line:84%
But could the scientists
have been tricked?

00:59:16.490 --> 00:59:19.530 align:middle line:84%
>>Skeptics are often unaware
of the amount of experience

00:59:19.530 --> 00:59:21.930 align:middle line:84%
and the amount of knowledge
that goes into investigations

00:59:21.930 --> 00:59:22.980 align:middle line:90%
of this kind.

00:59:22.980 --> 00:59:24.940 align:middle line:84%
Between the three
investigators, you

00:59:24.940 --> 00:59:26.950 align:middle line:84%
could say we've had
50 years and more.

00:59:26.950 --> 00:59:28.860 align:middle line:90%
We know all the tricks.

00:59:28.860 --> 00:59:32.030 align:middle line:10%
>>I don't see how
it could be faked.

00:59:32.030 --> 00:59:32.830 align:middle line:90%
It's impossible.

00:59:32.830 --> 00:59:39.460 align:middle line:90%


00:59:39.460 --> 00:59:41.970 align:middle line:84%
>>Nevertheless, was it
possible for the Scole Group

00:59:41.970 --> 00:59:44.270 align:middle line:84%
to have perpetrated
a massive hoax?

00:59:44.270 --> 00:59:46.152 align:middle line:84%
>>These things are so
extraordinary that when

00:59:46.152 --> 00:59:47.610 align:middle line:84%
one tells them to
people who've not

00:59:47.610 --> 00:59:49.130 align:middle line:84%
had the experiences
themselves, they

00:59:49.130 --> 00:59:50.421 align:middle line:90%
think, oh, it must be trickery.

00:59:50.421 --> 00:59:53.750 align:middle line:84%
And the challenge then always
is, OK, you duplicate it.

00:59:53.750 --> 00:59:56.340 align:middle line:90%


00:59:56.340 --> 01:00:00.850 align:middle line:84%
>>But so far, no one has
been able to do this.

01:00:00.850 --> 01:00:04.380 align:middle line:84%
Nevertheless, critics still
claim that the events at Scole

01:00:04.380 --> 01:00:08.390 align:middle line:84%
were produced by the kinds of
conjuring tricks used by stage

01:00:08.390 --> 01:00:10.710 align:middle line:90%
magicians and entertainers.

01:00:10.710 --> 01:00:13.940 align:middle line:84%
>>You fan them in this
manner, like this, you see?

01:00:13.940 --> 01:00:16.720 align:middle line:84%
>>Because professional
magicians learned all the skills

01:00:16.720 --> 01:00:18.950 align:middle line:90%
of illusion and misdirection--

01:00:18.950 --> 01:00:20.450 align:middle line:84%
>>I'm not going to
show you how it's

01:00:20.450 --> 01:00:22.366 align:middle line:84%
done, because if I showed
you how it was done,

01:00:22.366 --> 01:00:23.520 align:middle line:90%
you'd tell everybody else.

01:00:23.520 --> 01:00:27.390 align:middle line:84%
>>They are also well-qualified
to detect this type of fraud.

01:00:27.390 --> 01:00:28.190 align:middle line:90%
[SNAPPING]

01:00:28.190 --> 01:00:29.230 align:middle line:90%
>>Presto.

01:00:29.230 --> 01:00:31.320 align:middle line:84%
>>With that in
mind, James Webster

01:00:31.320 --> 01:00:36.300 align:middle line:84%
was invited to scrutinize
a number of Scole sessions.

01:00:36.300 --> 01:00:38.870 align:middle line:10%
Webster is a member of the
Magic Circle in Britain,

01:00:38.870 --> 01:00:42.890 align:middle line:10%
and has been a professional
magician for over 40 years.

01:00:42.890 --> 01:00:47.160 align:middle line:84%
>>Well, I had an opportunity
to view the cellar.

01:00:47.160 --> 01:00:51.560 align:middle line:84%
I could see no magic
props or anything

01:00:51.560 --> 01:00:54.160 align:middle line:84%
which made me feel
inclined to think

01:00:54.160 --> 01:00:57.170 align:middle line:90%
there was any hoax or trickery.

01:00:57.170 --> 01:01:00.440 align:middle line:84%
>>But could he replicate
the events at Scole?

01:01:00.440 --> 01:01:03.980 align:middle line:84%
>>I could not do it myself
as a professional magician.

01:01:03.980 --> 01:01:07.560 align:middle line:84%
And I don't believe that
any magician that I knew

01:01:07.560 --> 01:01:11.080 align:middle line:84%
could do even the lighting,
let alone the other phenomena

01:01:11.080 --> 01:01:11.880 align:middle line:90%
that I witnessed.

01:01:11.880 --> 01:01:16.740 align:middle line:90%


01:01:16.740 --> 01:01:18.680 align:middle line:84%
>>Any one of those
in the cellar,

01:01:18.680 --> 01:01:22.670 align:middle line:84%
I'd say they were wasting
their time doing this here,

01:01:22.670 --> 01:01:26.820 align:middle line:84%
for nothing, when they could be
earning a million dollars out

01:01:26.820 --> 01:01:27.620 align:middle line:90%
there on the stage.

01:01:27.620 --> 01:01:43.940 align:middle line:90%


01:01:43.940 --> 01:01:48.540 align:middle line:84%
>>In 1999, after an exhaustive
two-year investigation,

01:01:48.540 --> 01:01:51.190 align:middle line:84%
the investigators
published their conclusions

01:01:51.190 --> 01:01:53.405 align:middle line:84%
in the SPR's
official proceedings.

01:01:53.405 --> 01:01:58.060 align:middle line:90%


01:01:58.060 --> 01:02:00.350 align:middle line:84%
They were looking for
evidence of a hoax.

01:02:00.350 --> 01:02:03.970 align:middle line:84%
They sifted evidence
for signs of fakery,

01:02:03.970 --> 01:02:05.610 align:middle line:90%
but did they find it?

01:02:05.610 --> 01:02:08.190 align:middle line:10%
>>If you take all the
phenomena within the whole

01:02:08.190 --> 01:02:11.720 align:middle line:10%
of the Scole experiment over
two years while we were there,

01:02:11.720 --> 01:02:18.210 align:middle line:10%
I would say that the possibility
of fraud and faking was nil.

01:02:18.210 --> 01:02:20.390 align:middle line:84%
>>Although the Scole
report includes theoretical

01:02:20.390 --> 01:02:24.170 align:middle line:84%
discussions about how individual
phenomena might have been

01:02:24.170 --> 01:02:28.320 align:middle line:84%
faked, the chief investigators
concluded that events at Scole

01:02:28.320 --> 01:02:32.550 align:middle line:84%
cannot be explained either
by known scientific laws

01:02:32.550 --> 01:02:33.425 align:middle line:90%
or by trickery.

01:02:33.425 --> 01:02:37.390 align:middle line:90%


01:02:37.390 --> 01:02:39.500 align:middle line:10%
But Psychology
Professor Chris French,

01:02:39.500 --> 01:02:43.290 align:middle line:10%
the co-editor of Skeptic
Magazine, remains unconvinced.

01:02:43.290 --> 01:02:47.240 align:middle line:10%
>>There's lots of claimed
evidence for life after death

01:02:47.240 --> 01:02:48.650 align:middle line:10%
from lots of different sources.

01:02:48.650 --> 01:02:51.580 align:middle line:84%
The debate should be about
the quality of the evidence.

01:02:51.580 --> 01:02:53.830 align:middle line:84%
At the moment, on the basis
of the available evidence,

01:02:53.830 --> 01:02:57.310 align:middle line:84%
I'm not at all convinced that
there is such a thing as life

01:02:57.310 --> 01:02:59.380 align:middle line:90%
after death.

01:02:59.380 --> 01:03:02.290 align:middle line:84%
>>I think the skeptics regard
the possibility of the survival

01:03:02.290 --> 01:03:04.950 align:middle line:84%
of human consciousness
as inherently so

01:03:04.950 --> 01:03:08.860 align:middle line:84%
impossible that any one must
be rather crazy to believe it.

01:03:08.860 --> 01:03:10.660 align:middle line:84%
But you look at
the evidence, you

01:03:10.660 --> 01:03:13.860 align:middle line:84%
have to ask yourself whether
you'd be even more crazy not

01:03:13.860 --> 01:03:16.840 align:middle line:84%
to believe it, or to find some
alternative explanation which

01:03:16.840 --> 01:03:17.990 align:middle line:90%
makes any sort of sense.

01:03:17.990 --> 01:03:18.990 align:middle line:90%
And I haven't found one.

01:03:18.990 --> 01:03:25.000 align:middle line:90%


01:03:25.000 --> 01:03:28.630 align:middle line:84%
>>When we die, we go
into another world.

01:03:28.630 --> 01:03:34.200 align:middle line:90%
A lot of worlds, 3,665 worlds.

01:03:34.200 --> 01:03:36.350 align:middle line:90%
>>How can you be specific?

01:03:36.350 --> 01:03:38.853 align:middle line:84%
>>Because I read
it in the Bible.

01:03:38.853 --> 01:03:43.490 align:middle line:90%


01:03:43.490 --> 01:03:47.267 align:middle line:84%
>>News of the amazing events at
Scole spread around the world.

01:03:47.267 --> 01:03:51.840 align:middle line:90%


01:03:51.840 --> 01:03:54.960 align:middle line:84%
In 1997, they were
invited to hold sessions

01:03:54.960 --> 01:04:01.130 align:middle line:84%
in four European countries
and the United States.

01:04:01.130 --> 01:04:02.850 align:middle line:84%
Some of the most
successful sessions

01:04:02.850 --> 01:04:05.880 align:middle line:84%
occurred in the Los Angeles
home of Brian Hearst.

01:04:05.880 --> 01:04:08.510 align:middle line:84%
>>We wanted to see whether
it could also take place

01:04:08.510 --> 01:04:10.949 align:middle line:84%
so many thousands of
miles away from Scole

01:04:10.949 --> 01:04:12.115 align:middle line:90%
here in Southern California.

01:04:12.115 --> 01:04:14.840 align:middle line:90%


01:04:14.840 --> 01:04:18.480 align:middle line:84%
>>Hearst's converted garage was
the venue for eight sessions.

01:04:18.480 --> 01:04:21.936 align:middle line:84%
As many as 30 people
attended each one.

01:04:21.936 --> 01:04:22.736 align:middle line:90%
>>Hey.

01:04:22.736 --> 01:04:23.710 align:middle line:90%
>>Hi.

01:04:23.710 --> 01:04:23.970 align:middle line:90%
>>Hello, Cynthia.

01:04:23.970 --> 01:04:24.770 align:middle line:90%
Nice to see you.

01:04:24.770 --> 01:04:26.090 align:middle line:90%
>>Hi, how are you?

01:04:26.090 --> 01:04:26.990 align:middle line:90%
>>Great.

01:04:26.990 --> 01:04:29.510 align:middle line:84%
>>Before each session,
investigators carefully

01:04:29.510 --> 01:04:30.890 align:middle line:90%
inspected the room.

01:04:30.890 --> 01:04:32.690 align:middle line:84%
>>Many people went
in at different times

01:04:32.690 --> 01:04:36.390 align:middle line:84%
before the sessions, and
there was no paraphernalia.

01:04:36.390 --> 01:04:39.010 align:middle line:84%
There was nothing
hidden there at all.

01:04:39.010 --> 01:04:41.650 align:middle line:84%
>>Despite being interviewed
a decade after the Scole

01:04:41.650 --> 01:04:45.490 align:middle line:84%
experiment, these witnesses
are still profoundly moved

01:04:45.490 --> 01:04:46.700 align:middle line:90%
by what they saw.

01:04:46.700 --> 01:04:49.050 align:middle line:10%
>>There was so much
phenomena going on.

01:04:49.050 --> 01:04:50.212 align:middle line:90%
It was really overwhelming.

01:04:50.212 --> 01:04:53.830 align:middle line:90%


01:04:53.830 --> 01:04:55.800 align:middle line:84%
>>As with most
sessions, visitors

01:04:55.800 --> 01:04:58.770 align:middle line:84%
began by sitting quietly
in total darkness.

01:04:58.770 --> 01:05:02.350 align:middle line:84%
Then, they started hearing
the voices of the spirit team

01:05:02.350 --> 01:05:04.160 align:middle line:90%
speaking through the mediums.

01:05:04.160 --> 01:05:06.920 align:middle line:10%
>>Be quiet, be quiet, be quiet.

01:05:06.920 --> 01:05:07.950 align:middle line:90%
>>Marie.

01:05:07.950 --> 01:05:10.240 align:middle line:84%
>>Then the darkened
room burst into life.

01:05:10.240 --> 01:05:11.040 align:middle line:90%
>>Ain't that cool?

01:05:11.040 --> 01:05:11.950 align:middle line:90%
Look at that.

01:05:11.950 --> 01:05:12.840 align:middle line:90%
>>That is awesome.

01:05:12.840 --> 01:05:13.705 align:middle line:90%
>>Wow.

01:05:13.705 --> 01:05:14.580 align:middle line:90%
>>It's like a firefly

01:05:14.580 --> 01:05:16.230 align:middle line:90%
>>It's like fireworks.

01:05:16.230 --> 01:05:18.150 align:middle line:90%
>>Wow.

01:05:18.150 --> 01:05:20.950 align:middle line:84%
>>And then it would go up
to the rafters of the garage

01:05:20.950 --> 01:05:23.900 align:middle line:84%
and come down and thunk
