01:09:29.487 --> 01:09:32.050 align:middle line:84%
But some researchers
think there may be

01:09:32.050 --> 01:09:33.597 align:middle line:90%
another possible explanation.

01:09:33.597 --> 01:09:38.680 align:middle line:90%


01:09:38.680 --> 01:09:41.750 align:middle line:84%
Could some of the remarkable
events shown in this film

01:09:41.750 --> 01:09:44.420 align:middle line:84%
be the result of human
paranormal abilities

01:09:44.420 --> 01:09:47.990 align:middle line:84%
like psychokinesis, the
claimed ability of the mind

01:09:47.990 --> 01:09:50.313 align:middle line:90%
to directly affect matter.

01:09:50.313 --> 01:09:52.729 align:middle line:10%
>>There's an enormous amount
of evidence for the existence

01:09:52.729 --> 01:09:53.880 align:middle line:10%
of psychokinesis.

01:09:53.880 --> 01:09:55.870 align:middle line:84%
In the laboratory,
we're talking mainly

01:09:55.870 --> 01:09:59.870 align:middle line:84%
about the evidence of human
consciousness on random number

01:09:59.870 --> 01:10:03.600 align:middle line:84%
generators and very small events
that can be totally controlled.

01:10:03.600 --> 01:10:06.767 align:middle line:84%
There is clear evidence that
people can affect things.

01:10:06.767 --> 01:10:08.350 align:middle line:84%
>>One of the most
famous practitioners

01:10:08.350 --> 01:10:11.900 align:middle line:84%
of psychokinesis, or PK,
is a Russian housewife

01:10:11.900 --> 01:10:12.876 align:middle line:90%
called Nina Kulagina.

01:10:12.876 --> 01:10:15.672 align:middle line:90%


01:10:15.672 --> 01:10:18.190 align:middle line:84%
Kulagina was able to
demonstrate her abilities

01:10:18.190 --> 01:10:20.826 align:middle line:84%
under strictly controlled
conditions in front

01:10:20.826 --> 01:10:21.825 align:middle line:90%
of a team of scientists.

01:10:21.825 --> 01:10:25.890 align:middle line:90%


01:10:25.890 --> 01:10:28.830 align:middle line:84%
Researchers who investigated
her were convinced she

01:10:28.830 --> 01:10:33.520 align:middle line:84%
was able to do this solely
by the power of her mind.

01:10:33.520 --> 01:10:36.520 align:middle line:84%
So could the Scole Group and
their visitors unwittingly

01:10:36.520 --> 01:10:38.930 align:middle line:84%
have created some or
all of the phenomena

01:10:38.930 --> 01:10:41.000 align:middle line:90%
using mind over matter?

01:10:41.000 --> 01:10:43.720 align:middle line:84%
>>As an explanation, although
it's not more than just

01:10:43.720 --> 01:10:47.070 align:middle line:84%
simply a label to it, this
is psychokinesis and physical

01:10:47.070 --> 01:10:49.990 align:middle line:84%
mediumship, whether it is a
spirit working through someone,

01:10:49.990 --> 01:10:52.810 align:middle line:84%
a spirit acting
directly on an object,

01:10:52.810 --> 01:10:56.880 align:middle line:84%
or the medium's mind
causing the things to move.

01:10:56.880 --> 01:10:59.250 align:middle line:84%
>>Say there were real mind
over matter effects going

01:10:59.250 --> 01:11:02.130 align:middle line:84%
on as supposed to
conjuring tricks?

01:11:02.130 --> 01:11:03.630 align:middle line:84%
Then how do we know
they were coming

01:11:03.630 --> 01:11:05.680 align:middle line:84%
from the minds of the
disembodied people,

01:11:05.680 --> 01:11:07.810 align:middle line:84%
rather than from the
minds of the mediums who

01:11:07.810 --> 01:11:09.100 align:middle line:90%
were sitting in the room?

01:11:09.100 --> 01:11:12.780 align:middle line:84%
>>There is no definitive
answer to this question,

01:11:12.780 --> 01:11:14.700 align:middle line:84%
but the theory that
these phenomena were

01:11:14.700 --> 01:11:17.360 align:middle line:84%
due solely to psychokinesis
from the living

01:11:17.360 --> 01:11:21.640 align:middle line:84%
seems improbable, since PK
produced in laboratories

01:11:21.640 --> 01:11:24.190 align:middle line:90%
tends to be weak.

01:11:24.190 --> 01:11:26.720 align:middle line:84%
Therefore, mind over
matter from the living

01:11:26.720 --> 01:11:30.240 align:middle line:84%
is unlikely to explain the
huge range of phenomena

01:11:30.240 --> 01:11:31.644 align:middle line:90%
featured in this film.

01:11:31.644 --> 01:11:36.374 align:middle line:90%


01:11:36.374 --> 01:11:38.040 align:middle line:84%
>>Emily, when did you
live on the Earth?

01:11:38.040 --> 01:11:39.516 align:middle line:10%
>>Oh, a long time ago now.

01:11:39.516 --> 01:11:41.010 align:middle line:10%
>>19th century?

01:11:41.010 --> 01:11:42.160 align:middle line:10%
>>Yes.

01:11:42.160 --> 01:11:46.040 align:middle line:84%
>>We simply have a number
of clues of information

01:11:46.040 --> 01:11:49.360 align:middle line:84%
which was extremely
unlikely to have derived

01:11:49.360 --> 01:11:52.000 align:middle line:84%
from the subconscious
mind or the conscious mind

01:11:52.000 --> 01:11:53.840 align:middle line:90%
of the medium.

01:11:53.840 --> 01:11:56.190 align:middle line:84%
And the more
impressive those are,

01:11:56.190 --> 01:12:00.010 align:middle line:84%
the less likely it is that you
can say that this is an aspect

01:12:00.010 --> 01:12:03.210 align:middle line:84%
of mediumship, and the more
likely it is it's an aspect

01:12:03.210 --> 01:12:04.710 align:middle line:84%
of [? disconic ? ]
communication.

01:12:04.710 --> 01:12:13.244 align:middle line:90%


01:12:13.244 --> 01:12:15.160 align:middle line:84%
>>Previously, we traveled
with the Scole Group

01:12:15.160 --> 01:12:19.610 align:middle line:84%
to Italy, where they first
met with Marcelo Bacci.

01:12:19.610 --> 01:12:24.135 align:middle line:84%
They say they were able to talk
to the spirits via his radio.

01:12:24.135 --> 01:12:25.890 align:middle line:90%
>>Come on, who's this?

01:12:25.890 --> 01:12:26.690 align:middle line:90%
>>Come on, on here.

01:12:26.690 --> 01:12:30.600 align:middle line:90%


01:12:30.600 --> 01:12:31.400 align:middle line:10%
>>Timestream?

01:12:31.400 --> 01:12:33.970 align:middle line:90%


01:12:33.970 --> 01:12:35.460 align:middle line:84%
>>But when the
school group visited

01:12:35.460 --> 01:12:40.020 align:middle line:84%
Bacci in a later session,
he was having problems.

01:12:40.020 --> 01:12:42.090 align:middle line:84%
For months, hundreds
of people who

01:12:42.090 --> 01:12:45.030 align:middle line:84%
came from around the world
in the hope of hearing

01:12:45.030 --> 01:12:49.130 align:middle line:84%
their dead loved ones were
bitterly disappointed.

01:12:49.130 --> 01:12:52.600 align:middle line:90%
All they heard was static.

01:12:52.600 --> 01:12:54.490 align:middle line:90%
Bacci was depressed.

01:12:54.490 --> 01:12:57.021 align:middle line:84%
He feared he had lost
his unique talent.

01:12:57.021 --> 01:12:59.670 align:middle line:90%


01:12:59.670 --> 01:13:01.870 align:middle line:84%
Then, in an extraordinary
piece of luck,

01:13:01.870 --> 01:13:03.920 align:middle line:84%
as our cameras rolled
in an interview

01:13:03.920 --> 01:13:08.180 align:middle line:84%
with Bacci, the radio which
had been silent for so long,

01:13:08.180 --> 01:13:10.422 align:middle line:90%
burst into life.

01:13:10.422 --> 01:13:13.150 align:middle line:10%
>>[NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

01:13:13.150 --> 01:13:44.230 align:middle line:90%


01:13:44.230 --> 01:13:46.230 align:middle line:90%
>>Bacci's drought was over.

01:13:46.230 --> 01:13:49.514 align:middle line:84%
When the radio voice stopped,
there was celebration.

01:13:49.514 --> 01:13:50.430 align:middle line:90%
>>[NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

01:13:50.430 --> 01:13:53.590 align:middle line:90%


01:13:53.590 --> 01:13:55.720 align:middle line:84%
>>Bacci felt he'd
regained his ability

01:13:55.720 --> 01:13:57.550 align:middle line:90%
to communicate with the spirits.

01:13:57.550 --> 01:14:00.220 align:middle line:90%


01:14:00.220 --> 01:14:02.960 align:middle line:84%
But then joy turned
to disappointment

01:14:02.960 --> 01:14:06.140 align:middle line:84%
as he thought he had
failed to record the voice.

01:14:06.140 --> 01:14:08.050 align:middle line:10%
>>[NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

01:14:08.050 --> 01:14:23.390 align:middle line:90%


01:14:23.390 --> 01:14:25.520 align:middle line:84%
>>Once the recording
was transcribed,

01:14:25.520 --> 01:14:28.340 align:middle line:84%
Bacci told us the voice
belonged to a spirit

01:14:28.340 --> 01:14:31.520 align:middle line:84%
called Gregorio,
a Catholic Friar

01:14:31.520 --> 01:14:34.350 align:middle line:90%
who had died many years ago.

01:14:34.350 --> 01:14:37.660 align:middle line:84%
Later, independent
researcher Dr. Toriello,

01:14:37.660 --> 01:14:40.750 align:middle line:84%
read the last part of
this ghostly message.

01:14:40.750 --> 01:14:45.460 align:middle line:84%
>>Man, he passed he time
just deceiving himself.

01:14:45.460 --> 01:14:46.450 align:middle line:90%
OK.

01:14:46.450 --> 01:14:51.970 align:middle line:84%
But when all of you, you
will be here where we are,

01:14:51.970 --> 01:14:54.610 align:middle line:84%
then you will find answer
to all your questions.

01:14:54.610 --> 01:14:55.410 align:middle line:90%
I'm sorry.

01:14:55.410 --> 01:14:56.210 align:middle line:90%
I cannot say more.

01:14:56.210 --> 01:15:03.130 align:middle line:90%


01:15:03.130 --> 01:15:06.090 align:middle line:84%
>>We do look down our
friends and loved ones

01:15:06.090 --> 01:15:08.720 align:middle line:84%
after we die, until
such time as we move

01:15:08.720 --> 01:15:13.900 align:middle line:90%
on to some other dimension.

01:15:13.900 --> 01:15:15.800 align:middle line:84%
I think you can think
what you like, really.

01:15:15.800 --> 01:15:28.150 align:middle line:90%


01:15:28.150 --> 01:15:30.460 align:middle line:84%
>>Despite the evidence
from Scole and Bacci--

01:15:30.460 --> 01:15:33.880 align:middle line:90%


01:15:33.880 --> 01:15:36.720 align:middle line:84%
>>--most scientists still
refuse to even consider

01:15:36.720 --> 01:15:40.020 align:middle line:84%
the possibility that
consciousness might survive

01:15:40.020 --> 01:15:41.810 align:middle line:90%
death.

01:15:41.810 --> 01:15:44.600 align:middle line:84%
Dr. Rupert Sheldrake, the
internationally-renowned

01:15:44.600 --> 01:15:49.140 align:middle line:84%
biologist and Scole investigator
offers an explanation.

01:15:49.140 --> 01:15:51.410 align:middle line:84%
There's a dominant
materialism in science

01:15:51.410 --> 01:15:54.420 align:middle line:84%
that grew up in
the 19th century.

01:15:54.420 --> 01:15:56.830 align:middle line:84%
It's become part of
the culture of science,

01:15:56.830 --> 01:16:00.010 align:middle line:84%
but it's really a dogmatic
belief system rather than

01:16:00.010 --> 01:16:02.360 align:middle line:90%
a testable theory.

01:16:02.360 --> 01:16:04.040 align:middle line:84%
>>What this means
is that scientists

01:16:04.040 --> 01:16:06.460 align:middle line:84%
have become completely
focused on the things

01:16:06.460 --> 01:16:09.720 align:middle line:84%
they can both measure
and replicate in labs.

01:16:09.720 --> 01:16:12.610 align:middle line:84%
>>Within science, based on
the materialist point of view,

01:16:12.610 --> 01:16:15.620 align:middle line:90%
the mind is the brain.

01:16:15.620 --> 01:16:17.320 align:middle line:84%
So anything that
suggests the mind

01:16:17.320 --> 01:16:19.915 align:middle line:84%
might be more than the brain
goes against the theory,

01:16:19.915 --> 01:16:23.210 align:middle line:84%
and therefore most scientists
don't want to know about it.

01:16:23.210 --> 01:16:25.680 align:middle line:84%
>>Another prominent
scientist not convinced

01:16:25.680 --> 01:16:28.750 align:middle line:84%
that consciousness is solely
the result of brain activity

01:16:28.750 --> 01:16:30.550 align:middle line:90%
is Dr. Charles Tart.

01:16:30.550 --> 01:16:32.890 align:middle line:84%
>>That's just a small
part of the spectrum.

01:16:32.890 --> 01:16:35.870 align:middle line:84%
Dr. Tart is Emeritus
Professor of Psychology

01:16:35.870 --> 01:16:38.400 align:middle line:84%
at the University of
California and a leading

01:16:38.400 --> 01:16:41.520 align:middle line:84%
researcher into the evidence
for life after death.

01:16:41.520 --> 01:16:44.730 align:middle line:84%
>>The idea that survival of
bodily death is impossible

01:16:44.730 --> 01:16:48.560 align:middle line:84%
and that we're nothing
but our brains and bodies

01:16:48.560 --> 01:16:51.130 align:middle line:84%
is really a function of an
outmoded view in science,

01:16:51.130 --> 01:16:52.234 align:middle line:90%
a Newtonian worldview.

01:16:52.234 --> 01:16:55.510 align:middle line:90%


01:16:55.510 --> 01:16:57.520 align:middle line:84%
Now, the Newtonian
worldview works very well

01:16:57.520 --> 01:16:58.790 align:middle line:90%
for everyday events.

01:16:58.790 --> 01:17:01.610 align:middle line:84%
But one of the most interesting
things about modern science,

01:17:01.610 --> 01:17:05.451 align:middle line:84%
especially when you look at
stuff like quantum theory,

01:17:05.451 --> 01:17:07.742 align:middle line:84%
is that the world is far more
mysterious than we think.

01:17:07.742 --> 01:17:13.406 align:middle line:90%


01:17:13.406 --> 01:17:15.540 align:middle line:84%
And we now have
experimental evidence

01:17:15.540 --> 01:17:19.770 align:middle line:84%
of what Einstein called
spooky action at a distance,

01:17:19.770 --> 01:17:22.230 align:middle line:84%
that we could instantaneously
affect something

01:17:22.230 --> 01:17:24.190 align:middle line:84%
in a distant part
of the universe.

01:17:24.190 --> 01:17:26.510 align:middle line:90%
That's really wild.

01:17:26.510 --> 01:17:30.240 align:middle line:84%
If consciousness has any of
the qualities of this quantum

01:17:30.240 --> 01:17:33.740 align:middle line:84%
level of existence,
then phenomena

01:17:33.740 --> 01:17:35.991 align:middle line:84%
like survival of bodily
death are probably not

01:17:35.991 --> 01:17:36.990 align:middle line:90%
so mysterious after all.

01:17:36.990 --> 01:17:54.780 align:middle line:90%


01:17:54.780 --> 01:17:56.530 align:middle line:84%
But could quantum
theory explain one

01:17:56.530 --> 01:17:59.980 align:middle line:84%
of the most shocking
experiments conducted at Scole?

01:17:59.980 --> 01:18:02.060 align:middle line:84%
>>This particular
experiment was perhaps

01:18:02.060 --> 01:18:06.890 align:middle line:84%
the most important experiment
of the whole series.

01:18:06.890 --> 01:18:09.150 align:middle line:84%
>>Previously, we
showed how visitors

01:18:09.150 --> 01:18:14.966 align:middle line:84%
reported seeing these balls
of light appear before them.

01:18:14.966 --> 01:18:16.220 align:middle line:90%
>>It's like fireworks.

01:18:16.220 --> 01:18:19.920 align:middle line:84%
>>On this occasion, one of
them flew inside a large quartz

01:18:19.920 --> 01:18:20.720 align:middle line:90%
crystal.

01:18:20.720 --> 01:18:23.690 align:middle line:90%
>>The crystal then levitated.

01:18:23.690 --> 01:18:26.560 align:middle line:84%
We could see it glowing,
and then descended

01:18:26.560 --> 01:18:30.120 align:middle line:90%
into a Pyrex bowl.

01:18:30.120 --> 01:18:33.340 align:middle line:84%
Then Arthur Ellison was
invited to pick it up.

01:18:33.340 --> 01:18:36.173 align:middle line:84%
He picked it up and satisfied
himself that it was there,

01:18:36.173 --> 01:18:38.280 align:middle line:84%
and it was glowing, and
he put it down again.

01:18:38.280 --> 01:18:41.510 align:middle line:84%
He was asked right away to
pick it up again, he tried to,

01:18:41.510 --> 01:18:45.500 align:middle line:84%
and his fingers
closed right over it.

01:18:45.500 --> 01:18:47.500 align:middle line:90%
It had dematerialized.

01:18:47.500 --> 01:18:48.500 align:middle line:90%
>>There's nothing there.

01:18:48.500 --> 01:18:49.500 align:middle line:90%
Yes, it looks the same.

01:18:49.500 --> 01:18:51.104 align:middle line:90%
But there's nothing there.

01:18:51.104 --> 01:18:52.770 align:middle line:84%
>>Then he was asked
to pick it up again,

01:18:52.770 --> 01:18:53.970 align:middle line:84%
and it rematerialized
in his hand.

01:18:53.970 --> 01:18:54.770 align:middle line:90%


01:18:54.770 --> 01:18:57.396 align:middle line:90%
>>Ah, it feels crystal now.

01:18:57.396 --> 01:18:59.740 align:middle line:90%
>>Now, this dumbfounded him.

01:18:59.740 --> 01:19:01.850 align:middle line:84%
This is what finally
convinced him

01:19:01.850 --> 01:19:03.510 align:middle line:84%
that this was real,
because it couldn't

01:19:03.510 --> 01:19:04.920 align:middle line:90%
have been faked in any way.

01:19:04.920 --> 01:19:08.790 align:middle line:84%
And he had his head right
over the top of the bowl

01:19:08.790 --> 01:19:11.760 align:middle line:84%
in order to ensure that
no hand or no instrument

01:19:11.760 --> 01:19:15.137 align:middle line:90%
could interfere with it.

01:19:15.137 --> 01:19:16.970 align:middle line:84%
>>Of course, we were
totally amazed by this.

01:19:16.970 --> 01:19:19.466 align:middle line:84%
Things do not materialize
and dematerialize.

01:19:19.466 --> 01:19:21.090 align:middle line:84%
This is against all
the laws of nature.

01:19:21.090 --> 01:19:22.740 align:middle line:84%
We are trained
scientists, of course.

01:19:22.740 --> 01:19:24.330 align:middle line:84%
We know how the
world behaves, and it

01:19:24.330 --> 01:19:25.600 align:middle line:90%
doesn't behave like that.

01:19:25.600 --> 01:19:31.410 align:middle line:90%


01:19:31.410 --> 01:19:33.650 align:middle line:84%
>>But what does this
remarkable demonstration

01:19:33.650 --> 01:19:36.980 align:middle line:84%
tell us about what might
happen after death?

01:19:36.980 --> 01:19:39.460 align:middle line:84%
>>The spirit team told
us that the experiment

01:19:39.460 --> 01:19:44.310 align:middle line:84%
with the crystal in the bowl
